ments%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20meaning%20you%20can%20keep%20your%20monthly%20payments%20lower%20and%20more%20manageable.%20The%20trade-off%20is%20that%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20you%20would%20with%20shorter%20terms%2C%20like%20a%2015-year%20mortgage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%2215-Year%20Rates%5C%22%3ECurrent%2015-Year%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2F15-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E15-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20around%206%25%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow%20data.%20In%20October%2C%2015-year%20rates%20averaged%205.56%25%2C%20but%20they've%20been%20higher%20in%20recent%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20predictability%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20but%20are%20looking%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you.%20Because%20these%20terms%20are%20shorter%20and%20have%20lower%20rates%20than%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20you%20could%20potentially%20save%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest.%20However%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20than%20you%20would%20with%20a%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Refinance%20Rates%5C%22%3ECurrent%20Mortgage%20Refinance%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERefinance%20rates%20are%20also%20elevated.%20In%20October%2C%2030-year%20refinance%20rates%20averaged%206.35%25%2C%20while%2015-year%20refinance%20rates%20were%20around%205.67%25.%20They're%20even%20higher%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20Much%20Do%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Need%20to%20Drop%20to%20Refinance%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20wondering%20if%20you%20should%20refinance%20now%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20crunch%20the%20numbers%20to%20see%20if%20it%20makes%20sense.%20Some%20experts%20advise%20only%20refinancing%20