20in%20the%20arena.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELucius%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-lucius-gladiator-2-paul-mescal-first-movie-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaul%20Mescal%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20the%20son%20of%20Maximus%20and%20Lucilla%20(Connie%20Nielsen)%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20men%20who's%20forced%20to%20fight%20to%20the%20death%20in%20the%20Colosseum%20for%20the%20amusement%20of%20the%20emperors%20and%20the%20similarly%20bloodthirsty%20crowds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20scene%2C%20the%20Colosseum%20floor%20is%20flooded%20with%20water%20in%20honor%20of%20Poseidon%2C%20the%20god%20of%20the%20sea.%20To%20add%20to%20the%20danger%2C%20tiger%20sharks%20swim%20in%20the%20water%2C%20ready%20to%20feast%20on%20the%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENaval%20warfare%20ensues%20as%20two%20boats%20enter%20the%20arena%20to%20fight%20each%20other%2C%20the%20Romans%20versus%20Lucius%20and%20the%20other%20gladiators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boats%20circle%20the%20Colosseum%20before%20crashing%20into%20each%20other.%20Then%2C%20the%20men%20begin%20fighting%20viciously.%20As%20some%20of%20them%20fall%20off%20the%20boats%20and%20to%20their%20deaths%2C%20the%20sharks%20in%20the%20water%20swiftly%20tear%20them%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20far-fetched%20as%20the%20battle%20might%20seem%2C%20the%20scene%20was%2C%20at%20least%20partially%2C%20inspired%20by%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ee1ab74-6fa6-4234-a4de-7f5ab76f0f15%5C%22%3EStaged%20naval%20battles%20really%20did%20happen%20in%20Rome%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20naval%20battle%20taking%20place%20at%20the%20Colosseum%20in%20%26quot%3BGladiator%20II.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674099a69f2901eb603652bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20naval%20battle%20taking%20place%20at%20the%20Colosseum%20in%20%26quot%3BGladiator%20II.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EParamount%20Pictures%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWater%20spectacles%20in%20Rome%20go%20back%20to%20the%20first%20century%20BC.%20Areas%2C%20including%20the%20Colosseum%2C%20were%20flooded%20with%20water%20for%20staged%20fights.%20These%20mock%20naval%20battles%2C%20known%20as%20naumachia%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D04ff3496a4c9c3369828792b8ee3795be53c974fbd415ff489deb4398da68d15%26postID%3D673f9079cb042e5dec139928%26postSlug%3Dgladiator-2-sharks-naval-battle-colosseum-real-life-accuracy-2024-11%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nationalgeographic.com%252Fhistory%252Fhistory-magazine%252Farticle%252Froman-mock-naval-sea-battles-naumachia%2B%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebegan%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20Julius%20Caesar's%20rule%20in%20Rome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DTB5weRIYhjQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Geographic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%2080%20AD%2C%20two%20naumachiae%20took%20place%2C%20one%20in%20an%20artificial%20lake%20and%20another%20in%20the%20Colosseum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DTB5weRIYhjQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunclear%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20water%20entered%20the%20Colosseum%20via%20aqueducts%20or%20the%20arena's%20sluice%20gates%20and%20chambers%20that%20were%20used%20to%20drain%20and%20fill%20the%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20quite%20amazing%2C%26quot%3B%20Neil%20Corbould%2C%20special%20effects%20supervisor%20Neil%20Corbould%20of%20Industrial%20Light%20and%20Magic%2C%20said%20in%20the%20production%20notes%20for%20the%20film.%20%26quot%3BThe%20boats%20they%20used%20in%20these%20battles%20were%20built%20only%20for%20that%20purpose.%20They%20were%20flat-bottomed%20because%20the%20water%20was%20so%20shallow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlison%20Futrell%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20Roman%20history%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Arizona%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20Colosseum's%20enclosed%2C%20limited%20size%20meant%20that%20actual%20boats%20were%20probably%20%26quot%3Bcumbersome%20to%20maneuver%26quot%3B%20around%20the%20arena.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20staged%20naval%20battles%20at%20the%20Colosseum%20could%20work%20if%20the%20boats%20were%20sized%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20smaller%20sort%20of%20quasi-miniaturized%20boats%20that%20give%20the%20flavor%20of%20warships%20and%20that%20maybe%20accommodate%20greater%20visibility%20for%20the%20specifics%20of%20the%20combat%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Futrell%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20there%20are%20fans%20who%20want%20to%20really%20see%20what%20kind%20of%20fighting%20is%20going%20on%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227aa20efb-da82-44a8-8f43-e6f060c21945%5C%22%3EThe%20battles%20probably%20didn't%20include%20sharks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Water%20flooding%20the%20Colosseum%20in%20%26quot%3BGladiator%20II.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6740ad34fa0140cdd564e885%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22793%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWater%20flooding%20the%20Colosseum%20in%20%26quot%3BGladiator%20II.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EParamount%20Pictures%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHistory%20shows%20that%20people%20in%20Rome%20were%20at%20least%20aware%20that%20sea%20creatures%20existed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20encyclopedists%20from%20antiquity%20who%20talk%20about%20sea%20creatures%2C%20and%20they're%20aware%20of%20shark-like%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Futrell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Futrell%20said%20that%20these%20shark-like%20creatures%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20located%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20rather%20than%20the%20Mediterranean.%20Plus%2C%20most%20of%20the%20sea%20animals%20referenced%20were%20mammals%2C%20not%20fish%20like%20sharks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFutrell%20said%20that%20the%20Romans%20were%20aware%20of%20dolphins%20and%20orcas%2C%20which%20are%20both%20mammals.%20That%20said%2C%20there%20isn't%20a%20lot%20of%20evidence%20that%20the%20Romans%20were%20regularly%20building%20tanks%20big%20enough%20to%20allow%20people%20to%20interact%20with%20the%20creatures%20up%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20they%20knew%20about%20them%20as%20a%20draw%20and%20did%20make%20some%20effort%20at%20certain%20points%20in%20time%20to%20make%20them%20a%20kind%20of%20show%20in%20some%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20Futrell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20evidence%20that%20in%20one%20such%20instance%2C%20under%20Emperor%20Claudius'%20rule%2C%20an%20orca%20traveled%20to%20the%20Tiber%20River%20and%20some%20effort%20was%20made%20to%20turn%20the%20event%20into%20a%20spectacle%20by%20blocking%20off%20access%20points%20so%20people%20could%20see%20the%20creature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sharks%20featured%20in%20%26quot%3BGladiator%20II%26quot%3B%20are%20most%20likely%20an%20addition%20from%20Scott%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Few.com%2Fjoseph-quinn-fred-hechinger-crafting-delicious-gladiator-2-villains-8729456%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etends%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20include%20animals%20in%20his%20movies.%20There%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20be%20any%20historical%20evidence%20of%20sharks%20being%20part%20of%20these%20naval%20battles%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProbably%20not%20sharks%2C%20specifically%2C%20and%20only%20rarely%20orca%2C%26quot%3B%20Futrell%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20challenging%20to%20work%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BGladiator%20II%26quot%3B%20is%20now%20playing%20in%20theaters.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgladiator-2-sharks-naval-battle-colosseum-real-life-accuracy-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%2