0they%20have%20been%20for%20much%20of%20this%20year%2C%20while%20still%20spending%20on%20the%20holiday%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20still%20that%20desire%20to%20find%20lower-cost%20alternatives%20where%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Tassin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetailers%20and%20consumer%20brands%20reported%20this%20summer%20that%20shoppers%20%E2%80%94%20even%20affluent%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshoppers-spending-less-retailers-brands-cutting-prices-economy-explained-why-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epulling%20back%20on%20their%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20prices%20remained%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20consumers%20didn't%20stop%2C%20however.%20Rather%2C%20they%20tried%20to%20get%20more%20for%20their%20money%20%E2%80%94%20think%20shopping%20for%20clothes%20at%20an%20off-price%20store%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnordstrom-rack-results-show-shoppers-are-in-for-deals-discounts-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENordstrom%20Rack%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20one%20of%20the%20retailer's%20department%20stores%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Bank%20of%20America%20Institute%20report%20published%20last%20week%2C%20there%20are%20some%20signs%20that%20consumer%20conditions%20have%20improved%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20University%20of%20Michigan's%20Consumer%20Sentiment%20Index%20has%20been%20inching%20up%20since%20July.%20In%20October%2C%20the%20measure%20hit%20its%20highest%20mark%20since%20April.%20Credit%20card%20spending%20in%20states%20affected%20by%20Hurricanes%20Helene%20and%20Milton%20rebounded%20in%20the%20weeks%20after%20the%20storms%20in%20October%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20inflation%20has%20slowed%20on%20some%20essential%20goods%2C%20such%20as%20groceries%2C%20and%20even%20turned%20into%20deflation%20in%20others%2C%20such%20as%20gasoline%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%20Theoretically%2C%20that%20means%20shoppers%20have%20more%20money%20to%20spend%20on%20discretionary%20purchases%2C%20such%20as%20eating%20out%20and%20buying%20gifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIs%20the%20apparent%20strengthening%20in%20consumer%20spending%20temporary%3F%20Potentially%2C%20but%20there%20are%20reasons%20to%20be%20optimistic%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriday's%20retail%20sales%20growth%20showed%20%26quot%3Ba%20good%20early%20step%20forward%20into%20the%20holiday%20shopping%20season%2C%26quot%3B%20National%20Retail%20Federation%20Chief%20Economist%20Jack%20Kleinhenz%20said.%20Sales%20were%20up%200.4%25%20on%20a%20seasonally%20adjusted%20basis%20year-over-year%20in%20October%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau.%20The%20Bureau%20also%20revised%20its%20September%20sales%20figure%20upward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFalling%20energy%20prices%20have%20likely%20provided%20extra%20dollars%20for%20household%20spending%20on%20retail%20merchandise%2C%26quot%3B%20Kleinhenz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalmart%20and%20Target%2C%20which%20posted%20differing%20results%20this%20week%2C%20both%20provided%20evidence%20that%20consumers%20are%20still%20spending%20%E2%80%94%20if%20cautiously%20%E2%80%94%20going%20into%20the%20holidays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalmart%20CEO%20Doug%20McMillon%20said%20Tuesday%20that%20the%20chain%20gained%20share%20as%20shoppers%20with%20household%20incomes%20over%20%24100%2C000%20kept%20visiting%20its%20stores.%20Shoppers%20%26quot%3Bcontinue%20to%20seek%20value%20to%20maximize%20their%20budgets%2C%26quot%3B%20CFO%20John%20Rainey%20said.%20The%20company%20raised%20guidance%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20its%20fiscal%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarget%2C%20however%2C%20cut%20its%20outlook%20for%20the%20rest%20of%202024%20on%20Wednesday%20after%20the%20chain%20said%20that%20shoppers%20cut%20back%20on%20discretionary%20purchases%20during%20the%20third%20quarter.%20Chief%20Commercial%20Officer%20Rick%20Gomez%20said%20that%20Target%20is%20cutting%20prices%20on%202%2C000%20items%20and%20offering%20affordable%20gifts%2C%20such%20as%20a%20holiday%20toy%20selection%20with%20half%20of%20the%20items%20priced%20under%20%2420.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20prices%20are%20still%20higher%20than%20they%20were%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20said%20Morning%20Consult's%20Tassin%20said.%20That%20could%20push%20many%20consumers%20to%20look%20for%20value%20when%20they%20buy%20gifts%20or%20plan%20holiday%20parties%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20clear%20majorities%20of%20shoppers%20are%20willing%20to%20spend%20on%20gifts%2C%20food%20and%20beverages%2C%20and%20parties%20during%20the%20holidays%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpro.morningconsult.com%2Fanalyst-reports%2F2024-holiday-shopping-trends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Morning%20Consult%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20in%20late%20August%20and%20early%20September.%20Some%20were%20even%20willing%20to%20go%20into%20debt%20or%20cut%20back%20spending%20on%20essentials%20to%20afford%20their%20holiday%20plans%2C%20according%20to%20the%20survey%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20feel%20the%20financial%20pressure%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20that%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20spend%2C%26quot%3B%20Tassin%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20people%20might%20cut%20back%20on%20spending%20in%20other%20areas%20to%20ensure%20they%20have%20enough%20for%20their%20holiday%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20pay%20more%20attention%20to%20sales%2C%20or%20I'll%20buy%20the%20cheaper%20meat%20options%20so%20that%20I%20have%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20wiggle%20room%20to%20afford%20other%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshoppers-willing-to-spend-this-holidays-still-seek-deals-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%