ing%20cancer%20patients%20and%20their%20caregivers.%20She%20also%20dedicates%20time%20to%20Karunashraya%20(Bangalore%20Hospice%20Trust).%20She%20provides%20home-based%20palliative%20care%20counselling%20to%20end-of-life%20patients%20under%20the%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20Youth%20Movement%20(SVYM).%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20extensive%20volunteer%20work%20includes%20counselling%20for%20NGOs%20such%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Dignity%20Foundation%20(supporting%20the%20elderly)%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Helping%20Hand%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Youth%20for%20Seva%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20%E2%80%98The%20Art%20of%20Living%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20she%20has%20worked%20with%20inmates%20in%20Bangalore%20Central%20Jail.%20She%20has%20also%20collaborated%20with%20%E2%80%98Copewithcancer%20%E2%80%93%20Madat%20Trust%E2%80%99%20at%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s%20Tata%20Memorial%20Hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Talk%20to%20them%20as%20people%2C%20not%20patients%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20National%20Centre%20for%20Disease%20Informatics%20and%20Research%2C%20one%20in%20nine%20people%20in%20India%20is%20likely%20to%20face%20a%20cancer%20diagnosis%20at%20some%20point%20in%20their%20lives.%20Beyond%20its%20physical%20toll%2C%20cancer%20profoundly%20affects%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2Fvideo%2Ftop-mental-health-expert-do-you-need-help-get-free-counselling-find-support-manage-stress-more%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%20and%20emotional%20well-being%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20psychological%20support%20vital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20cancer%20patient%20needs%20a%20counsellor%20to%20help%20them%20cope%2C%E2%80%9D%20Alpa%20emphasises.%20She%20points%20out%20that%20families%20often%20withhold%20the%20diagnosis%20from%20patients%2C%20fearing%2